Types of Ecosystem
There are two main sorts of ecosystems. Listed under are the sorts and examples of the surroundings.

Natural atmosphere – It is a evidently produced biological surroundings located in nature. It consists of deserts, forests, grasslands, lakes, mountains, ponds, rivers, oceans, and many others.
Artificial environment – It is an artificial environment which is created and maintained through guy. It includes an aquarium, crop fields, gardens, parks, zoo, and so on.
The components of the surroundings are mainly divided into two classes.

Biotic environment–It consists of all living organisms inclusive of animals, birds, forests, insects, reptiles and microorganisms like algae, micro organism, fungus, viruses, and many others.
Abiotic environment– It includes all non-dwelling components including air, cloud, dust, land, mountains, rivers, temperature, humidity, water, water vapour, sand, and so on.
